- Why?

1306
01:06:07,186 --> 01:06:10,353
- It's like someone else
was doing it.

1307
01:06:10,354 --> 01:06:12,305
- Well, I wish somebody else
was doing it.

1308
01:06:12,306 --> 01:06:14,161
Now they're gonna think
we're all crazy.

1309
01:06:14,162 --> 01:06:15,761
- Oh, they're gonna love this.

1310
01:06:15,762 --> 01:06:17,424
"There's no racism.

1311
01:06:17,425 --> 01:06:19,377
They're doing it to themselves."

1312
01:06:19,378 --> 01:06:22,673
The press is gonna be
all over this.

1313
01:06:22,674 --> 01:06:25,809
Do you know that brothers
are being executed for nothing?

1314
01:06:25,810 --> 01:06:27,984
For nothing!

1315
01:06:27,985 --> 01:06:32,145
It's shit like this
that sets us back every time.

1316
01:06:32,146 --> 01:06:35,632
I can't believe I've got to go
on the air and report this.

1317
01:06:35,633 --> 01:06:37,713
This is an embarrassment!

1318
01:06:37,713 --> 01:06:38,737
- It's not about you.

1319
01:06:38,738 --> 01:06:41,361
- Well, it sure
as hell isn't about you.

1320
01:07:21,298 --> 01:07:23,153
- What are you gonna do?

1321
01:07:30,578 --> 01:07:32,432
- You?

1322
01:07:52,146 --> 01:07:54,641
- Good luck to you then, Sarah.

1323
01:07:54,642 --> 01:07:56,817
- Good luck to you.

1324
01:08:32,305 --> 01:08:34,224
- Write up a press release.

1325
01:08:34,225 --> 01:08:35,664
Don't say "expelled."

1326
01:08:35,665 --> 01:08:37,552
- I'll say he
voluntarily agreed to leave.

1327
01:08:37,553 --> 01:08:38,865
- Mm-hmm.

1328
01:08:38,866 --> 01:08:41,841
And say we've encouraged him
to seek counseling.

1329
01:08:41,842 --> 01:08:43,344
- Say he's deranged.

1330
01:08:43,345 --> 01:08:45,424
- You've never even spoken
to him.

1331
01:08:45,425 --> 01:08:48,528
- Highlight the fact
that we are forming a committee

1332
01:08:48,529 --> 01:08:51,377
and we're looking forward
to further discussion.

1333
01:08:51,378 --> 01:08:53,041
And you fill in the rest.

1334
01:08:53,042 --> 01:08:55,057
- I'll get it out this morning.

1335
01:08:57,617 --> 01:09:00,017
- You know, I feel sorry
for Simon.

1336
01:09:00,018 --> 01:09:02,448
I feel like it's going
to take him a long time

1337
01:09:02,449 --> 01:09:03,472
to recover from this.

1338
01:09:03,473 --> 01:09:05,617
- I think
he just wanted attention.

1339
01:09:05,618 --> 01:09:07,761
- None of you know Simon.

1340
01:09:07,762 --> 01:09:09,232
- I do.

1341
01:09:09,233 --> 01:09:10,641
He's Little Black Sambo.

1342
01:09:10,642 --> 01:09:12,880
That's how he referred
to himself in the notes.

1343
01:09:12,881 --> 01:09:14,705
Remember the story?

1344
01:09:14,705 --> 01:09:17,521
Little Black Sambo
has some beautiful new clothes,

1345
01:09:17,522 --> 01:09:18,992
and he's walking
through the jungle

1346
01:09:18,993 --> 01:09:20,113
showing them off,

1347
01:09:20,113 --> 01:09:21,808
and a tiger jumps out
of the bush

1348
01:09:21,809 --> 01:09:22,801
and threatens to eat him.

1349
01:09:22,802 --> 01:09:26,928
So Little Black Sambo
offers his coat

1350
01:09:26,929 --> 01:09:30,097
to the tiger
in exchange for his life.

1351
01:09:30,098 --> 01:09:32,368
And then another tiger pops up,
and so on and so on,

1352
01:09:32,369 --> 01:09:34,833
until the tigers have taken
all his clothes.

1353
01:09:34,834 --> 01:09:39,024
Little Black Sambo is going home
naked and forlorn

1354
01:09:39,025 --> 01:09:42,032
when he hears a terrible noise
coming from the forest.

1355
01:09:42,033 --> 01:09:44,049
All of the tigers
are wearing his clothes

1356
01:09:44,050 --> 01:09:45,393
And arguing over
which of them

1357
01:09:45,394 --> 01:09:47,601
is the grandest tiger of all.

1358
01:09:47,601 --> 01:09:49,392
The tigers argued and argued

1359
01:09:49,393 --> 01:09:51,825
until they got so angry,
they started chasing each other

1360
01:09:51,826 --> 01:09:52,944
around a tree.

1361
01:09:52,945 --> 01:09:54,577
They began spinning and spinning

1362
01:09:54,578 --> 01:09:56,368
Until they were
just a yellow blur.

1363
01:09:56,369 --> 01:09:57,552
They spun so fast,

1364
01:09:57,553 --> 01:09:59,824
they spun themselves
into butter.

1365
01:09:59,825 --> 01:10:02,704
So Little Black Sambo
got himself a spoon,

1366
01:10:02,705 --> 01:10:05,872
scooped up the butter,
and ate the tigers up,

1367
01:10:05,873 --> 01:10:08,112
which is just what Simon Brick
has done to us,

1368
01:10:08,113 --> 01:10:10,736
gotten us all in a whirl
over nothing.

1369
01:10:10,737 --> 01:10:12,881
- It wasn't over nothing.

1370
01:10:12,882 --> 01:10:14,865
- He's a little fox,
a con man.

1371
01:10:14,866 --> 01:10:17,681
- Imagine him
for half a second.

1372
01:10:17,682 --> 01:10:18,833
- Oh, ho.

1373
01:10:18,834 --> 01:10:20,817
- That isn't why he did it.

1374
01:10:20,818 --> 01:10:22,192
- Why then?

1375
01:10:23,602 --> 01:10:24,624
- I don't know.

1376
01:10:24,625 --> 01:10:25,840
- You don't know?

1377
01:10:27,953 --> 01:10:28,848
- Come in.

1378
01:10:31,633 --> 01:10:33,105
- I got a call you wanted
to see Simon

1379
01:10:33,106 --> 01:10:34,224
before I drive him home.

1380
01:10:34,225 --> 01:10:35,889
- Yes, we do.
- Oh, please don't.

1381
01:10:35,890 --> 01:10:37,297
- We deserve an opportunity

1382
01:10:37,298 --> 01:10:40,817
to confront the individual
who's put us through all this.

1383
01:10:40,818 --> 01:10:42,448
Bring him in here, Mr. Meyers.

1384
01:11:00,529 --> 01:11:02,320
Well,
don't you have anything

1385
01:11:02,321 --> 01:11:03,792
to say for yourself,
Mr. Brick?

1386
01:11:03,793 --> 01:11:05,808
What were you trying
to get out of us?

1387
01:11:08,785 --> 01:11:09,937
- Nigger.

1388
01:11:12,754 --> 01:11:15,601
I was waiting for someone
to call me a nigger.

1389
01:11:18,193 --> 01:11:19,856
- You see, all my life,
my dad told me,

1390
01:11:19,857 --> 01:11:21,457
"be ready.

1391
01:11:21,458 --> 01:11:23,344
Be ready for the day.
Be ready."

1392
01:11:23,345 --> 01:11:24,752
But no one would do it.

1393
01:11:24,753 --> 01:11:26,961
- Because no one
on this campus thinks that.

1394
01:11:26,962 --> 01:11:28,657
- Yeah.

1395
01:11:28,657 --> 01:11:32,176
Everyone on this campus
is real nice to me.

1396
01:11:32,177 --> 01:11:36,112
I mean, I walk into a room,
and you all smile big smiles.

1397
01:11:36,113 --> 01:11:37,648
And I can see
you're all trying really hard

1398
01:11:37,649 --> 01:11:39,952
to think of something
to say to me,

1399
01:11:39,953 --> 01:11:42,800
going out of your way
to be my friend,

1400
01:11:42,801 --> 01:11:45,137
like my R.A.

1401
01:11:45,138 --> 01:11:46,257
He's great.

1402
01:11:46,258 --> 01:11:47,856
You know he has dinner
with me every night?

1403
01:11:47,857 --> 01:11:49,905
I can't even walk down
the sidewalk

1404
01:11:49,906 --> 01:11:51,376
because every one
of my professors

1405
01:11:51,377 --> 01:11:53,904
has to come up to me
and say hello.

1406
01:11:53,905 --> 01:11:56,145
They walk right past
all their white students,

1407
01:11:56,145 --> 01:11:58,000
but they all say hello to me.

1408
01:11:58,001 --> 01:11:59,505
Yeah, I'm--

1409
01:11:59,506 --> 01:12:02,161
I'm lucky
the way everyone loves me.

1410
01:12:02,162 --> 01:12:03,824
- You are lucky.

1411
01:12:03,825 --> 01:12:06,992
- You think I can't feel
that hate?

1412
01:12:06,993 --> 01:12:09,552
It's so thick
that I can't even breathe!

1413
01:12:09,553 --> 01:12:11,921
Why don't you just say it?

1414
01:12:11,922 --> 01:12:13,201
Say it!

1415
01:12:13,202 --> 01:12:14,352
- Get him out of here.

1416
01:12:14,353 --> 01:12:15,825
- Come on, Simon, let's go.
- Say it!

1417
01:12:15,826 --> 01:12:17,521
- Get him out of here.
Get him off my campus now.

1418
01:12:19,793 --> 01:12:22,032
- I hate you too.

1419
01:12:22,033 --> 01:12:22,929
- Let's go.

1420
01:12:41,201 --> 01:12:43,216
- And on that note...

1421
01:12:46,642 --> 01:12:48,336
- What's this?

1422
01:12:48,337 --> 01:12:50,096
- My letter of resignation.

1423
01:12:50,097 --> 01:12:51,249
I quit.

1424
01:12:51,250 --> 01:12:52,464
- Why?

1425
01:12:52,465 --> 01:12:54,384
- This sends
a terrible message.

1426
01:12:54,385 --> 01:12:55,632
- He's right.

1427
01:12:55,633 --> 01:12:57,712
He's nothing but a problem
to you.

1428
01:12:57,713 --> 01:12:59,152
- Of his own making.

1429
01:12:59,153 --> 01:13:00,624
- You're relieved he's gone.

1430
01:13:00,625 --> 01:13:02,704
You'd be relieved
if they all left.

1431
01:13:02,705 --> 01:13:04,785
- That's outrageous.

1432
01:13:04,786 --> 01:13:07,057
- Oh, there's no cameras now.
Just say it.

1433
01:13:07,058 --> 01:13:09,841
"We'd all be so much happier.

1434
01:13:09,842 --> 01:13:14,512
It'd be so much easier
if everybody was white."

1435
01:13:14,513 --> 01:13:17,265
- I have never thought that.
- Fine.

1436
01:13:17,266 --> 01:13:19,408
Stick to your stories
if it makes you feel better,

1437
01:13:19,409 --> 01:13:21,520
but...

1438
01:13:21,521 --> 01:13:24,177
I don't want
to be a liar anymore,

1439
01:13:24,178 --> 01:13:26,672
and I really want
to get the fuck out of here.

1440
01:13:28,978 --> 01:13:30,801
- Where are you going?

1441
01:13:38,033 --> 01:13:39,664
- Hey, jared.
Wait up.

1442
01:13:39,665 --> 01:13:42,288
- Oh, thanks.

1443
01:13:42,289 --> 01:13:43,185
- There it is.

1444
01:13:45,169 --> 01:13:48,400
Come here.

1445
01:13:48,401 --> 01:13:50,608
Congratulations.

1446
01:13:50,609 --> 01:13:52,560
Send me a postcard
from the land of the living.

1447
01:13:52,561 --> 01:13:55,057
- All right.

1448
01:13:55,058 --> 01:13:56,112
Bye.

1449
01:14:00,049 --> 01:14:02,192
- Dean Daniels.

1450
01:14:02,193 --> 01:14:04,112
Greg Sullivan,
Students for Tolerance.

1451
01:14:04,113 --> 01:14:05,840
- Oh, yeah,
I remember you, Greg.

1452
01:14:05,841 --> 01:14:06,800
What's up?

1453
01:14:06,801 --> 01:14:08,816
- Our first meeting was a bust.

1454
01:14:08,817 --> 01:14:12,464
Dean Strauss wouldn't shut up.

1455
01:14:12,465 --> 01:14:13,648
- And on top of that,

1456
01:14:13,649 --> 01:14:15,472
there are no black students
in our group.

1457
01:14:15,473 --> 01:14:17,328
- Aha.
- Right.

1458
01:14:17,329 --> 01:14:18,480
It's ridiculous.

1459
01:14:18,481 --> 01:14:21,136
But I don't know what to do.

1460
01:14:23,762 --> 01:14:25,392
- Well, maybe I do.

1461
01:14:37,873 --> 01:14:39,121
- Hi, Dean Daniels.

1462
01:14:39,122 --> 01:14:41,616
- Hey,
Claudia, Tyler.

1463
01:14:41,617 --> 01:14:43,312
I've got someone here
I'd like you to meet.

1464
01:14:44,689 --> 01:14:46,768
- I think Aaron's point
that we cover these stories

1465
01:14:46,769 --> 01:14:49,744
more aggressively
is probably true,

1466
01:14:49,745 --> 01:14:53,392
but they also seem un--
unusually common.

1467
01:14:53,393 --> 01:14:56,497
- But it's fair to speculate
on what motivates these people.

1468
01:14:56,498 --> 01:14:58,417
Belmont is implying
that this particular student

1469
01:14:58,418 --> 01:14:59,377
is mentally ill.

1470
01:14:59,378 --> 01:15:00,560
- Well,
of course you have to be

1471
01:15:00,561 --> 01:15:02,161
to do something like this.

1472
01:15:02,162 --> 01:15:03,825
But it happens often enough

1473
01:15:03,826 --> 01:15:05,841
that it makes you wonder

1474
01:15:05,842 --> 01:15:08,752
if there's not
something else too.

1475
01:15:08,753 --> 01:15:10,096
- Something in the air?

1476
01:15:10,097 --> 01:15:11,888
- Well, maybe.

1477
01:15:11,889 --> 01:15:14,000
I mean, this kid wouldn't have
done this to himself

1478
01:15:14,001 --> 01:15:16,368
if somebody hadn't made him
feel bad,

1479
01:15:16,369 --> 01:15:18,640
if somebody hadn't put the words
in his head.

1480
01:15:18,641 --> 01:15:21,168
See, I don't think
you see yourself like that,

1481
01:15:21,169 --> 01:15:22,480
the way he did,

1482
01:15:22,481 --> 01:15:26,480
unless somebody's already seen
you that way first.

1483
